{"id":14881822,"mediaExerciseId":"4647fc73-4e39-4b43-99c4-772707e274a2","exerciseName":"6","chapterName":"23","chapterTitle":"Enterprise Risk Management","groupId":612487,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":786,"solutions":[{"id":6004739,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this question, we will discuss the advantages and disadvantages of using a futures contract vs. using call options. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"If they buy a futures contract, they may be negatively affected if the price of the commodity goes down. However, in a futures contract, the buyer does not have to pay for an expensive premium.\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/4b04f5187f5da64b69d3241bc39e3f15/200a025ec9c8682972504a37d8ac9b9c/lateximg_large.png","width":998},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/4b04f5187f5da64b69d3241bc39e3f15/200a025ec9c8682972504a37d8ac9b9c/lateximg.png","width":500}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"On the other hand, if they opt for a call option, a decrease in the price of the commodity will be beneficial. Additionally, they can opt not to exercise their option if the price is not in their favor. However, the offside of this is the expensive premium that they are going to pay for this option. \n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":141,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/4b04f5187f5da64b69d3241bc39e3f15/8df5d0f6aedd9fcfae89ef8c7d136c2d/lateximg_large.png","width":998},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/4b04f5187f5da64b69d3241bc39e3f15/8df5d0f6aedd9fcfae89ef8c7d136c2d/lateximg.png","wid